            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>County Convention</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p> The County Convention to nominate county officers and to select delegates to
                        the Congressional Convention to meet in Harrisonburg on the 5th of October
                        next, met in the Court house on last Monday--Maj. Wm. M. Tate, Chairman. The
                        Convention made the following nominations for county officers:<lb/>
                        Treasurer--Charles T. Cochran, <lb/>County Clerk--Wm. A. Burnett,
                        <lb/>Circuit Clerk--Joseph N. Ryan, <lb/>Commonwealth's Attorney--Jas.
                        Bungardner, <lb/>Supt. Of the Poor--George W. Fauber, <lb/>Sheriff--Wm. L.
                        Mowry, <lb/> Surveyor--Col. J.D. Lilley. </p>
                    <p>The following delegates were elected to represent this county in the
                        Congressional Convention to meet in Harrisonburg on the 5th day of October:</p>
                    <p>Beverly Manor Township--A.W. Harman, Jacob Baylor, Wm. J. Shumate, John N.
                        Opie, T.P. Eskridge, Lewis Harman, David Doom.</p>
                    <p>Middle River Township--S.C. Harper, T.J. Burke, C.S. Roller, J.D. Craig, Wm.
                        Crawford, C.S. Grattan, S.B. Finley, G. Barnhart.</p>
                    <p>North River Township--J.G. Fulton, James A. Hamrick, T.S. Hogshead, Wm.
                        Gamble, D.N. Vanlear, John H. Ervin, James G. Turk.</p>
                    <p>Riverheads Township--A.B. Turk, T.M. Smiley, J.D. Lilley, A. Blauth, M.W.D.
                        Hogshead, A.A. Sprout, W.T. Rush, J.D. McGuffin.</p>
                    <p>Staunton Ward No. 1--Wm. B. Kaynes, Robt. Burke, Wm. G. Sterrett, R. Maury.</p>
                    <p>Staunton Ward No. 2--Wm. A. Burke, M.H. Effinger, S. Travers Phillips, M.G.
                        Harman.</p>
                </transcript>
